==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Straightedge
<hw>Straight"edge`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A board, or
piece of wood or metal, having one edge perfectly straight, -- used to
ascertain whether a line is straight or a surface even, and for drawing
straight lines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Straighten</ent>⟦br⟧
